<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#2373cbc64f2c6330724b80918b25fc45>.
<#2373cbc64f2c6330724b80918b25fc45> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.48723/0xhc-vp63>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-03-05T06:17:16.623Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#2373cbc64f2c6330724b80918b25fc45> {
<https://doi.org/10.48723/0xhc-vp63> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Multipel skleros"@sv, "Remitterande multipel skleros"@sv, "Multiple Sclerosis, Relapsing-Remitting"@en, "Multiple sclerosis"@en, "Antikropp"@sv, "Antibody"@en, "GlialCam"@sv, "GlialCam"@en, "Epstein Barr Virus"@sv, "Epstein Barr Virus"@en, "ANO2"@sv, "ANO2"@en, "CRYAB"@sv, "CRYAB"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__710.
_:b0__710 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/c795e170654102e79b6afc8870e38530>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.48723/0xhc-vp63> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/NON_PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002973>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Dessa data genererades med hjälp av plasmaprover från EIMS-studien (1). Det övergripande målet med EIMS studien är att förstå vilka livstil och genetiska faktorer som påverkar MS risk. Denna delstudies mål var att bättre förstå hur epstein barr virus kan påverka uppkomst av autoimmuna reaktioner. Studien inkluderar data från 661 populationsbaserade kontroller och 650 multipel sklerospatienter från Sverige. Datan består av antikroppsnivåer mätta med fluorescensaktiverad pärlbaserad analys. Prover kördes i duplikat. Nivåerna justerades mellan plattorna med användning av batchkontrollprover. De angivna värdena är medelvärdet av de två körningarna efter batchkorrigering.\nHLA-genotyper har imputerats från SNP-genotyper i HlA-regionen av kromosom 6 med hjälp av HLA*IMP:02 som beskrivits tidigare (2).\n\nDatasetet består av följande filer:\n- PNAS_Data_combined.csv (433 kB)\n- MetaData.csv\n- MetaDescription.docx\nMer information om variablerna i tabellerna finns i dokumentationsfilen."@sv, "This data was generated using plasma samples from the EIMS study (1). The overall goal of the EIMS study is to understand which lifestyle and genetic factors influence MS risk. The aim of this sub-study was to better understand how epstein barr virus can affect the onset of autoimmune reactions. The study includes data from 661 population based controls and 650 multiple sclerosis patients from Sweden. The data consists of antibody levels estimated using fluorescence-activated bead-based assay. Samples were run in duplicate. The levels were adjusted between plates using batch controlled samples. The values given are the average of the two run samples after batch correction.\nHLA genotypes have been imputed from SNP genotypes in the HlA region of chromosome 6 using HLA*IMP:02 as described previously (2). \n\nThe dataset contains of the following files:\n- PNAS_Data_combined.csv (433 kB)\n- MetaData.csv\n- MetaDescription.docx\nDetails about the variables in the tables can be found in the documentation file"@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/2661886>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/3e1ed125832c8fbcee484db07addcc33>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.48723/0xhc-vp63#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2025-02-12T10:22:01.243278Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.48723/0xhc-vp63>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2026-03-03T12:31:24.150273Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Antikroppsnivåer mot Epstein Barr-virusantigen och molekylära sekvenshomologa proteinter hos patienter med multipel skleros och kontroller"@sv, "Antibody levels towards Epstein Barr virus antigens and molecular mimics in multiple sclerosis patients and controls"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/HEAL>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__2143.
_:b0__2143 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "2024"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "2005"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>.
<https://doi.org/10.48723/0xhc-vp63> a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#86b4de1267182815dc22f4ec24b78244>.
<#86b4de1267182815dc22f4ec24b78244> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.48723/enwx-zn78>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-03-05T06:17:16.624Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#86b4de1267182815dc22f4ec24b78244> {
<https://doi.org/10.48723/enwx-zn78> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Neurologi"@sv, "Neurology"@en, "Pediatrik"@sv, "Pediatrics"@en, "Cerebral pares"@sv, "Cerebral Palsy"@en, "Arbetsterapi"@sv, "Occupational Therapy"@en, "CEREBRAL PALSY"@en, "CEREBRAL PARES"@sv;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__370.
_:b0__370 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/986780ba446fb1022ebd7cdc039908fd>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.48723/enwx-zn78> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__6561.
_:b0__6561 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/a90f973af7cfe6eec54681f2d270e141>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.48723/enwx-zn78> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/NON_PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002973>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Detta var en kluster-randomiserad, kontrollerad, enkelblind studie på en kohort av barn och ungdomar med CP i Iganga-Mayuge Health and Demographic Surveillance Site. CP-kohorten var uppdelad i två armar: en som fick Akwenda-interventionsprogrammet och den andra fungerade som kontroll i väntan på att få interventionen följande år. Barn med epilepsi i båda grupperna fick anti-epileptiska läkemedel. Resultaten utvärderades före och efter interventionsperioden.\n\nData har samlats in innan interventionen startade (2021; baslinje) och efter att interventionen på 12 månader avslutades (2022).\n\nRandomiserad, kontrollerad, interventionsstudie.\n\nBasdata: Sociodemografisk information och kliniska data inklusive antropometri, nivåer för klassificeringssystem för grov motorik (GMFCS).\n\nPrimärt utfall: Picture My Participation (PMP); frekvens av närvaro och nivå av engagemang i 20 dagliga aktiviteter.\n\nDatasetet består av följande filer:\n- Data sharing PMP Akwenda.xlsx (48,7 kB)\n- Documentation file data sharing PMP.docx\nMer information om variablerna i tabellerna finns i dokumentationsfilen."@sv, "This was a cluster-randomized, controlled, single-blinded study on a cohort of children and young people with CP in the Iganga-Mayuge Health and Demographic Surveillance Site. The CP cohort was divided in two arms: one receiving the Akwenda Intervention program, and the other serving as control waiting to receive the intervention the following year. Children with seizures in both groups were provided anti-seizure medications. Outcomes were assessed prior to and after the intervention period.\n\nThe Excel sheet includes the data collected before the intervention started (2021; baseline), and after the 11 months intervention ended (2022; follow-up).\n\nRandomized, controlled, intervention trial.\n\nBaseline data: Sociodemographic information and clinical data including anthropometry, Gross Motor Function Classification System (GMFCS) levels.\n\nPrimary outcome:  Picture My Participation (PMP); frequency of attendance and level of involvement in 20 activities of daily living.\n\nThe dataset contains of the following files:\n- Data sharing PMP Akwenda.xlsx (48.7 kB)\n- Documentation file data sharing PMP.docx\nDetails about the variables in the tables can be found in the documentation file."@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/226074>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.48723/enwx-zn78#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2025-01-29T10:11:15.304788Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.48723/enwx-zn78>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2026-03-03T13:36:03.346794Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Data för: Participating outcome of  Akwenda Intervention Program for children with cerebral palsy in Uganda"@sv, "Data for: Participating outcome of Akwenda Intervention Program for children with cerebral palsy in Uganda"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/HEAL>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__860.
_:b0__860 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "2022-11-30"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "2021-07-01"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>
}

